    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Plants that are cultivated for food, typically restricted to the edible parts of a herbaceous plant (such as leaves, stems, or roots) that are traditionally served as a savory course of a meal.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
